<p><strong>Longsword</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Straight Swords" href="/Straight+Swords" target="">Straight Sword</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Longsword</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for melee users who want to remain mobile during combat.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A straight sword with a double-edged blade. <br>In addition to its easily-inflicted standard damage, this well- <br>balanced weapon can also perform powerful piercing attacks. </em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Longsword in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Longsword weapon can be found at the following locations:&nbsp;</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Starting equipment for the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Vagabond" href="/Vagabond" target="">Vagabond</a> class.</li> 
 <li>Can be purchased from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Twin Maiden Husks" href="/Twin+Maiden+Husks" target="">Twin Maiden Husks</a>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1,000&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes" target="">Runes</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Longsword Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Square Off" href="/Square+Off">Square Off</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a> and buffed with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Longsword</strong>&nbsp;can be upgraded by using&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones">Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Compared to the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lordsworn's Straight Sword" href="/Lordsworn's+Straight+Sword" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lordsworn's Straight Sword</a>,&nbsp;the Longsword&nbsp;has lower base damage, critical damage rating and range. However, under Flame Art, Sacred and Magic infusions, the Longsword&nbsp;has better elemental damage scaling than the Lordsworn's Straight Sword.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;<img title="Sell Value" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px.png" alt="item value icon elden ring wiki guide 18px" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100</li> 
</ul> 
<p>The <strong>Longsword</strong> can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>. Click below for a list of all possible Ashes of War that can be applied to the straight sword.</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <details> 
