				<li id="16411738" class="cmnt-root" data="-35" data-d="1644888239000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t576364/Longsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Feb 2022 20:23</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16411738" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is not a Longsword as its blade simply isn&apos;t long enough though its also not an Arming Sword which is what people usually erroneously call a Longsword as it actually has a proper two-handed Longsword handle. Its a strange mixture of the two. The short blade of an Arming Sword and the Long two-handed grip of a Longsword (and in this game unlike the former Souls games it is a proper two-handed grip not just an extended grip). Can&apos;t say I&apos;ve seen that before...interesting. Incorrect name but still interesting.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16411738" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16411738" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">5</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>15</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>50</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col